<translate>
<!--T:11-->
{{Caption|The BIM Views Manager}}

==Usage== <!--T:6-->

<!--T:7-->
The BIM Views Manager will show all the levels (building parts) and working plane proxies of your document. It can be docked anywhere in the FreeCAD interface or be left in a standalone window. Building Parts will also show their level (the Z-coordinate of their placement).

<!--T:8-->
* Clicking the '''BIM Views Manager''' button in the Status Bar shows or hides the BIM Views Manager.

===Top part=== <!--T:14-->

<!--T:12-->
* Clicking any entry selects the corresponding object.
* Double-clicking the height of a level allows you to edit it.
* Double-clicking the name of any object sets the working plane to it and activates the object {{Version|1.1}}. If the '''Restore View''' property of the object is set to True, and a view configuration has been stored in it, that viewpoint is also restored.
* The BIM Views Manager top half has a right-click context menu with the following options:
** '''Activate''' activates a selected level.
** '''New Level''' creates a new [[Arch_BuildingPart|level]].
** '''New Working Plane Proxy''' creates a new [[Draft_WorkingPlaneProxy|working plane proxy]].
** '''Delete''' deletes a selected item.
** '''Toggle Visibility''' turns a selected level on/off (same as the Space bar).
** '''Isolate''' turns all levels off except the selected one.
** '''Save View Position''' stores the current view settings in the selected object, allowing to restore it if its '''Restore View''' property is set to True.
** '''Rename''' allows you to rename a selected object.

===Bottom part=== <!--T:15-->

<!--T:13-->
* Double-clicking a drawing orients the 3D view to the drawing.
* Double clicking a page opens or activates the page tab.


